<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,230,761]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,222,230,256]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Shrubs</emphasis>
, branches tomentose, inermous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[599,694,230,256]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Nectary</emphasis>
absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[791,886,230,256]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Stipules</emphasis>
lateral, triangular. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1106,1188,230,256]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Leaves</emphasis>
bipinnate, paripinnate, 3–foliolate, leaflets opposite, oblong, venation actinodromous, translucid punctuation absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1197,1355,266,292]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Inflorescence</emphasis>
raceme, axillary. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[236,331,302,328]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Flowers</emphasis>
pedicellate, actinomorphic, diplostemonous; calyx gamosepalous, sepals 5, corolla gamopetalous, tubular, rose, petals 5; androecium monadelphous, heterodinamous, anthers longitudinal; ovary superior, sessile, pluriovulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[285,347,374,400]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Fruit</emphasis>
legume, sessile, linear, plane, margin straight, epicarp glabrous, brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1158,1225,374,400]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Seeds</emphasis>
not observed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
