<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,230,761]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,525,482,508]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
The species is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[831,902,482,508]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, found in the Northeast region (PE, BA), in the Caatinga and Atlantic Rainforest domains (
<bibRefCitation author="Flora do Brasil" box="[626,869,518,544]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" refId="ref15971" refString="Flora do Brasil 2020 (2020) Fabaceae. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. [http: // reflora. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 115]" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry box="[732,799,518,544]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was found recently by (
<bibRefCitation author="Gomes, A. S. &amp; Rodrigues, E. M. &amp; Queiroz, R. T. &amp; Moura, D. C. &amp; Melo, J. I. M." pageId="9" pageNumber="26" pagination="191 - 194" refId="ref16175" refString="Gomes, A. S. Rodrigues, E. M., Queiroz, R. T., Moura, D. C. &amp; Melo, J. I. M. (2020) First Record of Calliandra subspicata (Fabaceae) in Paraiba State, Brazil. Harvard Papers in Botany 25: 191 - 194. https: // doi. org / 10.3100 / hpib. v 25 iss 2.2020. n 6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Gomes 
<emphasis box="[1394,1452,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
) to Paríba state.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,230,761]" box="[189,910,590,616]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,590,616]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers in August and December.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,230,761]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,496,626,652]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1875" box="[496,756,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subspicata">
<emphasis box="[496,756,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Calliandra subspicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized, mainly, by the shrub habit, raceme inflorescences, monadelphous androecium, bipinnate leaves, legume with straight margin. Morphologically, it is distinguished from all other species found in the area, sharing with some the presence of bipinnate leaves and flowers with monadelphous androecium, feature of the species of the Ingeae tribe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
